          <declname>out_mesh_data</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the latest occlusion mesh. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Returns <ref refid="struct_m_l_occlusion_mesh" kindref="compound">MLOcclusionMesh</ref> with its latest data. When doing consecutive calls and there was no mesh update, the same data will be returned. The memory is owned by the system. Application should copy the data it needs to cache.</para>
<para>Every call to <ref refid="group___occlusion_1ga587477a06bf01038c6a61d9222a2284c" kindref="member">MLOcclusionGetLatestMesh()</ref> must be followed by a matching call to <ref refid="group___occlusion_1gaa567e649b61cc2fdf29101a068126130" kindref="member">MLOcclusionReleaseMesh()</ref>, otherwise this method will return an error.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>API Level:\n 28</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
